The German-US car maker DaimlerChrysler said Tuesday sales of its prestigious Mercedes brand rose slightly in the first quarter of the current year on a 12-month basis. "Mercedes group sales are up slightly in the first quarter," a company spokesman confirmed board member Juergen Hubbert as saying at a product launch in Majorca. In January and February alone, Mercedes sales edged forward by two percent to 164,100 cars and for the year as a whole the Mercedes brand is forecasting stable sales and earnings. spm/hd Germany-US-auto-company-results-DaimlerChrysler 